metadata.name: Vaporwave Hotel #20
metadata.description:
This set is a love letter to mass-produced geometric 1980s Hotel Art.

There a 150 editions with a mint price of 0.2 TEZ
which is essentially a giveaway so get greedy ok?

Why so low?

It is my Genesis on FXHash and also my first p5js coding project.

I recommend that you spend 1 TEZ total, mint 5 and burn any boring ones, 
flip one or two on to secondary, and HODL those super-rare gems for yourself.

I dedicate this piece to NapoleonBonaparte.tez, who took the time to help me get started on this path. Thank you Napoleon!

Hope you enjoy the play of color & shape, alongside a heavy dose of nostalgia and retro vibes. 

To heighten your experience, feel free to read this poem as you view your 1/1 art from this collection.

"Unlock the secrets, discover hidden pleasures, indulge your desire for rich color and bold designs. The Vaporwave Hotel collection by HP LoveBux. Check it out, and Check into a whole new level of luxury and satisfaction. Vaporwave Hotelon FXHash ... You're worth it."

Sincerely,
Hp LoveBux

metadata.name: Chromatic Waves #213
metadata.description:
Threads of color are weaved together, interacting and vibrating.

SVG generated with JavaScript.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 3200×2400.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=3200&h=1800 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width and h the desired height. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: fabrics #74
metadata.description:
'fabrics' explores textile art made with code mixing different patterns of very small lines.

Inspiration from Anni Albers works, Antoni Tàpies and Studio Yorktown for the patterns and the colours. Also oriental rugs and clothes from around the world had been used for the palettes.
Palettes: Monochrome, Kilt, Kilim, Austral, Peruvian, Afghan, Berber, Nain, Fur, Jeans, Kente, Bogolan, Albers, Sabler.

Press [s] to save an 1200x1360 image (.png).
Click on it to change the orientation of the stitches.

Generative art made using p5js. By @mehno_art

metadata.name: Interlaced #16
metadata.description:
From African tribal clothes to Islamic mosaics every civilization throughout history has produced delicate patterns to share the essence of their culture. These artifacts have changed our understanding of how art, like societies form through bonds, the very fabric of things that have become symbols for cycles, paths and relationships.

Interlaced explores these unique motifs using emergent algorithms to produce colorful continuous patterns. The project uses a dynamic engine that traverses triangular meshes placing diverse tile configurations. By combining art with technology, the project aims to tell a new story of making digital connections between geography, culture and time.

Press “s” to save in high-resolution.

metadata.name: Liquid Eternal (Painting Machine) #2
metadata.description: "Liquid Eternal" is the second installment in my Painting Machine series, which aims to translate painterly techniques through generative code. The algorithm for this piece produces a composition of brushstrokes, splatters, and gestures that will continue transforming indefinitely. While the FxPreview command creates a snapshot of the piece at a specific moment in time, the work itself defies any notion of a completed image.

metadata.name: Memo #101
metadata.description:
Memo is a abstract expression of memories written on small pieces of paper, pictures of important moments or a reminder of all the things You have forgotten.

Memo is created with P5JS. Large number of rectangles are packed in loops to the canvas with a random rectangle packing algorithm with simple collision detection. 
The looped area varies from 1 vertical or horizontal rectangle to 8x8 grid. Packed area is created with simple random walking grid loop.
60+ color palettes are handpicked and they can appear reversed. 
One random palette is picked for each piece and p5js.noise() drives the colors, size and angle on the rects with lots of attributes.

Click 'n' to add white noise.
Click 's' to save image as jpeg.

Click '1' to 1x pixelDensity(3600 x 6400 or 6400 x 3600 px - default).
Click '2' to 2x pixelDensity(7200 x 12800 or 12800 x 7200 px).

VGA 2022 / CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Flow #408
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022
